OL,3,CEd Davey calls for return of 'family
OL,4,Cdoctor' by giving over-70s named GP
OL,6,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey
OL,7,Fhas set out plans to give everyone
OL,8,Fover 70 and those with long-term
OL,9,Fhealth conditions access to a named GP.
OL,11,FThe policy would affect around 18.7
OL,12,Fmillion people in this cohort, who
OL,13,Fhave been found to benefit the most
OL,14,Ffrom having continuity of care.
OL,16,FThe party pointed to British Medical
OL,17,FJournal research showing that people
OL,18,Fwho had kept the same GP for more than
OL,19,F15 years had a 25% lower chance of
OL,20,Fdying than those with a GP
OL,21,Frelationship lasting a year or less.
